Everything we ate at @manhattanbcdtofu was delicious. Literally EVERYTHING! Don’t even get us started on the Spicy Raw Crabs! 😋😋😋⁣
⁣
@bcdtofuhouse was founded in 1996 by Mrs. Hee Sook Lee, a first generation Korean immigrant, in Koreatown in Los Angeles. There are now over 13 locations in the country.⁣

@sevenacredairyco is the newest must-see spot in #PaoliWI.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Originally a cheese factory built in 1888 before it closed in 1980, it has been restored into a one-of-a-kind destination by local entrepreneurs with the intent of preserving its Wisconsin heritage. It is now in the National Register of Historic Places.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
The beautifully restored space has a Dairy Cafe, an Inn, and a Kitchen that hosts Chef’s Counter Tasting experiences (seen here) with a menu that changes weekly.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
We’ll post about their Dairy Cafe soon, so stay locked on our feed!⁣⁣⁣

Don’t know why we’ve been sitting on this video for as long as we have, but here it is 😁⁣⁣
⁣⁣
@amaramadisonwi serves their take on Contemporary Coastal Italian cuisine and you can find them at @hilldalemadison in #MadisonWI.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
They have a a great bar with aperitifs, negronis, cocktails, and espresso as their specialty. They do have Italian wines as well. If you’re not a fan of booze, they also have non-alcoholic cocktails… even kombucha!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We recommend trying the “Pan Fried Lasagna” which has 102 layers (it really does), and their “Osso Buco”. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have you dined here yet? ⁣⁣

🚨@daveshotchicken is finally in Madison!🚨⁣
⁣
You can find them at 4814 Annamark Dr in #MadisonWI, where the old Hardee’s used to be on the East Side.⁣
⁣
There are 3 locations in Wisconsin: Milwaukee, Menomonee Falls, and Madison.⁣
⁣
It’s fast-casual dining here. You order at the counter, you get a number, wait for it to be called, and pick up your order at the counter. ⁣
⁣
You get to choose from 7 levels of spice:⁣
⁣
No Spice⁣
Lite Mild⁣
Mild⁣
Medium⁣
Hot⁣
Extra Hot⁣
Reaper (you must sign a waiver for this one)⁣
⁣
Check them out when you can and tell us about it in the comments 😃⁣

We were invited to check out @easttownkitchenandbar in #MilwaukeeWI which is conveniently located inside the Milwaukee Marriott Downtown @marriotthotels.⁣

We ordered everything that the Chef suggested and really enjoyed everything. The standouts are the Shrimp & Grits and the Fried Bologna Sandwich. We’d come back for those two any time. The Bacon Jar filled with house-smoked pork belly is a must!⁣
⁣
We definitely plan to go back to try their breakfast and brunch menu VERY soon.⁣

@sparkssteakhouse in #NewYorkCity is known for their aged beef, fine wines, and for the variety of seafood that they carry for a steak house.⁣
⁣
Sparks started out as an English pub on East 18th Street owned by a man named Don Sparks (hence the name) before it was purchased by the Cetta brothers in 1966 and converted into a steakhouse. They moved it to its current location on East 46th street in 1977. ⁣
⁣
The restaurant has a pretty dark history, as it’s also known for the location where Gambino crime family boss “Big Paul” Castellano and underboss Thomas Bilotti were gunned down in 1985. The hit was given under the orders of John Gotti.⁣
⁣
Have you dined here before? Let us know in the comments 😃⁣

@ozby.oz has officially become our new fave bar in #MadisonWI 💯⁣

⁣
They have yummy snacks (OMG The French Onion Dip 🤤) and non-alcoholic beverages available. They can pretty much make any beverage for you and the staff is great! We just love it here ❤️⁣
⁣
Oh, and bonus… @settledowntavern is just a few feet away 😁⁣
⁣
⁣

The Rice Noodle Rolls from @yinjichangfen_nyc came in clutch after walking around #ChinatownNYC.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It’s casual dining here and food comes out swiftly. This spot fills up fast, but not to worry, tables turn quickly and you can also order for takeout at the counter. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
They have other street food as well as congee here as well. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We definitely plan to come back and try everything on their menu. ⁣⁣
